<TITLE> Dhaka stocks surge in midday trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 2 (bdnews24.com) - Dhaka stocks surged in midday trade Monday, triggered by a rally in the shares of banks and power companies. The market went straight across the vertical line just after the beginning. It fell slightly due to profit-taking in the first hour but started upward until midday. The main index DGEN or general index climbed 36.87 points or 1.71 percent to 2186.19 at 12.11pm. The DSI or all-share price index gained 30.44 points or 1.72 percent to 1794.62. Gainers outnumbered losers 122 to 33. A total of 18 issues held steady. Turnover reached Tk 1.15 billion. On Thursday, the total turnover was Tk 1.34 billion. EXIM Bank, DESCO, BRAC Bank, Shahjalal Bank and Power Grid Company of Bangladesh topped on the turnover board at 11.54am. Buying pressure pulled all the shares up. EXIM Bank grew to Tk 421 from Thursday's Tk 390.5 on buying pressure. DESCO rose to Tk 995 from Tk 954.4 after it said it had a loan agreement with the Asian Development Bank on strengthening its electricity distribution network and upgrading and expanding its distribution system. BRAC Bank traded higher at Tk 775.5 from Tk 760. Shahjalal Bank rose to Tk 245 from Tk 234. Power Grid advanced to Tk 592 from Tk 584.5. The remaining top issues by turnover value were Pubali Bank, Grameen 1 MF, Southeast Bank, UCBL and Heidelberg Cement, trading higher. bdnew
